<P>
   MIDEAST-BARAK-ARAFAT (Erez Crossing, Gaza Strip) _ At this
sun-baked juncture between Israel and the Gaza Strip, the first
Israeli-Palestinian summit in seven months began Sunday with an
embrace and an exchange of gifts. Yasser Arafat, the Palestinian
leader, presented Ehud Barak, the new prime minister of Israel,
with a dove-shaped Hanukkah menorah. Barak gave Arafat a leather
boxed twin set containing the Koran and the Bible. By Deborah
Sontag. (With photo.)
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-PAKISTAN (New Delhi, India) _ India and Pakistan agree on
a withdrawal of Islamic militants from mountain redoubts on the
Indian side of Kashmir. By Celia Dugger and Barry Bearak.
</P>
