<P>
   WATCHDOGS _WASHINGTON _ Inside almost every corner of the
federal government, an army of about 15,000 waste-busters is
seeking out ways that taxpayers' money is squandered. At a cost of
about $2 billion a year, investigators, auditors, inspector
generals and congressional overseers churn out a constant flow of
warnings of federal waste, abuse and fraud. But given that some
problems fester despite years of admonitions, it's not clear if
anyone is listening or responding.(Malone, Cox News Service) 25.
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-IOWA _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush _ king of fund raising,
pope of the polls _ heads to Iowa this week looking for support in
next month's GOP straw poll. It's a disproportionately important
event that looks little like democracy. Participants have to pay to
vote or get a candidate to pay for them to vote. And one group
planning on having a major impact at the event is none-too-thrilled
with Bush's middle-of-the-road position on abortion. The head of
the Iowa Christian Coalition says a ``supermajority'' of its
members want nothing to do with a candidate who won't vow to have
an anti-abortion running mate. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED
</P>
