contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) _ ``American Pie'' captured the
biggest slice of business at the nation's multiplexes with a solid
$18.1 million at 2,508 theaters during the Friday-Sunday as the
coming-of-age comedy edged ``Wild Wild West,'' studio sources said
Sunday. by Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER-GIRLS (Los Angeles) _ She was the original soccer mom.
The American Youth Soccer Organization _ which is anticipating a
tidal wave of girls signing up at registration this fall _ traces
the roots of girls' soccer to 1971 in L.A.'s Granada Hills when
Jaymee Jusko and a handful of her friends began kicking around a
ball. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news files.)
</P>
</TEXT>
