<P>
   MICROSOFT-TEMPS (Seattle) _ Microsoft has improved benefits for
the contract workers who make up a third of its Puget Sound
workforce. But the workers' ongoing discontent _ along with two
potentially expensive lawsuits _ may compel the Redmond software
maker to eliminate or restructure this labor source. The change
could cause reverberations nationwide in the software industry and
other businesses needing a workforce that can grow or shrink to
match product lifecycles.
</P>
<P>
   By Dan Richman. (Story will move in the ``a'' and ``f''
categories.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-OWEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ ``John, we have too many
cookbooks.'' The first time my wife uttered that complaint, she was
gazing at 5,000 copies of the first ``Intermediate Eater
Cookbook,'' delivered to our basement. Today, Intermediate Eater
cookbooks are distributed by this newspaper. So when Alice
complains that we have too many cookbooks, she means the collection
of other people's books lining two walls of a study.
</P>
<P>
   By John Owen. (Story has moved in the ``d'' category.)
</P>
