<HEADLINE>
AS FUNNY AS A CRUTCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ What's it take to get a dislocated sense of
humanity? A hyperextended ego? Blinded by the spotlight of athletic
fame?
</P>
<P>
   Ask the football players at UCLA, where when you limp the whole
team limps with you.
</P>
<P>
   Who hasn't been hacked off trying to find a parking spot in
Westwood _ once, it even happened when we were going to the Special
Olympics at Drake Stadium. But there was no consideration, not one
thought, of stooping to pull in between the UCLA powder-blue lines
on the street.
</P>
<P>
   Our mamas only had to say it once: It just ain't right.
</P>
<P>
   The 14 football players who allegedly wrangled illegal
handicapped-parking placards exposed not so much an abhorrent abuse
of the system but that the system can be so abhorrently abused. It
also shows what a desperate college kid might do to save a few
hundred bucks in university parking fees.
</P>
<P>
   That's why the punishment that'll fit this crime is easy. After
a state judge is done with them, game suspensions by coach Bob
Toledo won't do. You can get suspended for hundreds of things in
college these days, sad to say.
</P>
<P>
   Unless someone finds real malice here instead of inconsiderate
stupidity, we endorse a bajillion hours of community service. Start
across the street at the VA Hospital, helping someone attach his
prosthetic legs and then drive him to the market.
</P>
<P>
   Where then you can park in the handicapped spot all day if you
want.
</P>
<P>
   _Oh, and by the way, if it's possible, the guys would hope that
in the future you refer to them as ``morally challenged.'' ...
</P>
<P>
   _The Stanford band called an emergency session to plan for the
halftime show of the Cardinal's home game Sept. 25 against UCLA....
</P>
<P>
   _A Monistat Moment: What we enjoy calling chick kickball,
Women's World Cupper Julie Foudy calls ``booters with hooters.''
Which is no endorsement of the restaurant/bar chain with
tight-shirted waitresses to be a title sponsor for a women's pro
league....
</P>
<P>
   _Who wouldn't want their daughter to grow up and be like Mia ?
Either Hamm or St. John....
</P>
<P>
   _The question isn't how much the Dodgers had to bribe Gary
Sheffield this year so he'd represent the team at the All-Star
Game. It's how much they had to bribe baseball to have someone
represent them at all....
</P>
<P>
   _Don't care what the roster limitations are, Roger Clemens , Mo
Vaughn and Wade Boggs should have been must-invites for an All-Star
Game in Fenway. Even ahead of Juan Gonzalez....
</P>
<P>
   _Bring back two All-Star Games per year, one for the fans' picks
at midseason and one later for the really deserving players....
</P>
<P>
   _Former Giants catcher Bob Brenly , named to the '84 NL All-Star
team, remembers before that game when Tom Lasorda , who was going
to coach third base, got up on a picnic table in the middle of the
clubhouse and shouted, ``Hey, everybody, let's go over the signs.''
Then San Diego Padres reliever Goose Goosage yelled back: ``Sit
down, Tommy. Everybody in the league already knows your signs.''
...
</P>
<P>
   _Just in case you were wondering: With 191 dingers, Eric Karros
has more home runs than any active player who has not ever made an
All-Star team....
</P>
<P>
   _Also, just in case you were wondering: Hack Wilson 's record
RBI count from 1930 is stuck on 191 this week....
</P>
<P>
   _Paul Konerko charged into the All-Star break on a 13-for-23
streak (.579)....
</P>
<P>
   _The Warriors have given former NoHo and Stanford guard Arthur
Lee a chance to play for their summer-league team in Long Beach....
</P>
<P>
   _Lakers players angling for a starring role in PhilJax's
triangle offense best hope that Scottie Pippen agrees to come over
and show 'em how it's done. See ya, Glenn Rice . Nice play, Robert
Horry . But we got a championship to win....
</P>
<P>
   _Jackson said that ``unless it's absolutely necessary for us to
fill a position that this team has a weakness in, Dennis Rodman
will not be our first choice.''
</P>
<P>
   That does, unfortunately, leave the door open for him to be a
very high runner-up choice.
</P>
</TEXT>
