   (NYT7) BOSTON -- July 11, 1999 -- BBO-MARTINEZ-PROFILE-2, 7-11
-- Pedro Martinez, 27, the star right-hander for the Boston Red
Sox, has 15 victories this season and doesn't think of himself as a
nearly perfect pitcher; he doesn't even believe he is the best
pitcher in his family. Martinez will start for the American League
in Tuesday night's All-Star game in Boston. Then later in the week,
he will begin the second half of the season slightly off a
30-victory pace. (C.J. Gunther/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) BOSTON -- July 11, 1999 -- BBO-MARTINEZ-PROFILE-1, 7-11
-- Pedro Martinez, 27, on the mound during a game against the
Chicago White Sox on April 15. Martinez, the star right-hander for
the Boston Red Sox, has 15 victories this season and has a chance
to become the first pitcher in more than three decades to win 30
