of HBO's highest-rated dramatic shows, has received mostly
favorable reaction. Others, however, have condemned it for its
violence. While broadcast network shows are divided into acts, each
ending in an artificial climax, ``Oz'' runs one hour straight on
HBO, a premium cable channel. ``With 'Oz' you can never break
away,'' saysFontana. ``It's unsettling in a good way.'' (Sara
