<P>
   (NYT3) NEW BRUNSWICK, N.J. -- July 11, 1999 --
BIGFILMS-SMALLBUCKS, 7-11 -- Loews is among the theater companies
investing in 'megaplexes,' which have big screens and stadium-style
seating, like the 17-screen complex, above and below, in New
Brunswick. Though audiences are flocking to the spacious
megaplexes, people are staying away in droves from the multiplexes
of shoe-box size theaters that have been a mainstay of shopping
malls and a staple of the industry for decades. So the big theatre
chains are attempting to convert multiplexes to megaplexes whenever
and wherever they can. (Norman Y. Lono/New York Times Photo)
</P>
