   JUDGE-WALD-PROFILE _ Judge Patricia Wald retires from the U.S.
Court of Appeals for the D.C. Circuit for a seat on the
international war crimes tribunals; long one of the most
influential federal judges, especially in matters of federal
regulation, and role model for a generation of women lawyers. By
Linda Greenhouse.
