<P>
   BIGFILMS-SMALLBUCKS (Undated) _ It's already shaping up as a
summer of movie blockbusters, with ``Star Wars,'' ``The Spy Who
Shagged Me'' and ``The Wild, Wild West'' already out and other
widely anticipated films like ``Eyes Wide Shut'' and ``The
Haunting'' still to come. And with so many ``megaplex'' cinemas
available, replete with big screens and so-called stadium seating,
filmgoers are having a better theater-going experience than ever.
So why are all of the main movie-theater companies all losing money
and their stocks all sagging? By Geraldine Fabrikant.
</P>
