   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following story for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Monday,
July, 12. If you have any questions, please call Patricia Hardin on
the Star's News Desk at (816) 234-4753.
RACE-VIOLENCE-2TAKES (Undated) Picture a white supremacist. Some
might see the stereotype that author Jessie Daniels describes in a
book on the topic: A ``beer-swilling, shotgun-toting, pickup
driving, gap-toothed, trailer dwelling, cousin-marrying'' half-wit.
Make way for Benjamin Smith. The man who carried out last weekend's
shooting rampage in Illinois and Indiana was the product of
affluence, quality schools and white-collar parents in Midwest
suburbia. Could he reflect, as some experts contend, a ``new
generation'' of well-heeled hatred? By RICK MONTGOMERY. Two takes.
Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
